.TH "pinctrl_get_device_gpio_range" 9 "pinctrl_get_device_gpio_range" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pinctrl_get_device_gpio_range \- find device for GPIO range
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" pinctrl_get_device_gpio_range
.BI "(unsigned gpio "  ","
.BI "struct pinctrl_dev **outdev "  ","
.BI "struct pinctrl_gpio_range **outrange "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "gpio" 12
the pin to locate the pin controller for
.IP "outdev" 12
the pin control device if found
.IP "outrange" 12
the GPIO range if found
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Find the pin controller handling a certain GPIO pin from the pinspace of
the GPIO subsystem, return the device and the matching GPIO range. Returns
-EPROBE_DEFER if the GPIO range could not be found in any device since it
may still have not been registered.
